I hit that bug too as I rebased another [still open] PR https://github.com/apache/incubator-superset/pull/4800/files#diff-fc9248d548b6023f93970ff78f529025R51

I'm hoping to merge this soon. Otherwise you can replicate the fix as another PR.

@john-bodley

I was following the same pattern for the Object.assign which is merging state and controls together. I've refactored it using the spread operator notation.
```
> a
{ foo: 'bar' }
> b
{ hugh: 'miles' }
> {...a, ...b}
{ foo: 'bar', hugh: 'miles' }
```
